      "id": 1,
      "text": "Founded August 30 1836 by brothers Augustus and John Allen at Buffalo Bayou, Houston was incorporated on June 5 1837.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1,
        13
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia",
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Houston"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The city is named after General Sam Houston, who secured Texas’s independence at San Jacinto just 25 miles east of Allen’s Landing.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Houston"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The Astrodome, dubbed the “Eighth Wonder of the World,” opened in 1965 as the world’s first indoor domed sports stadium.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        8
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Houston"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "After Galveston’s 1900 hurricane, the Houston Ship Channel was built, turning Houston into a major Gulf port.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Houston"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Rice University’s historic campus, founded in 1912, sits beside Hermann Park and the Texas Medical Center.",
